cs131.pa4.CarsTunnels

Class PreemptivePriorityScheduler

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs131.pa4.Abstract.Scheduler
      • cs131.pa4.CarsTunnels.PreemptivePriorityScheduler

  • public class PreemptivePriorityScheduler
extends Scheduler
    The preemptive priority scheduler assigns vehicles to tunnels based on their priority and supports ambulances. It extends the Scheduler class.

        public Tunnel admit(Vehicle vehicle)
        Description copied from class: Scheduler
        Attempts to admit the given vehicle in one of the scheduler's tunnels. If there is no tunnel available, the method should wait and try again when appropriate. This means that the method should only return if the vehicle was successfully admitted in one of the tunnels and return that tunnel.
        Specified by:
